reviews.text: Pizza was unexpectedly good. Crust was different than I've had before, but in a good way. BBQ chicken pizza was my favorite. Very flavorful. Standard cheese was solid as well. Great pizza spot in town.

Went here years ago, didn't see what all the fuss was about. Service was lacking and the pizza truthfully sucked.... Popped in today 7/25/25, the atmosphere was completely different, the fish tank is gone,seems better decorated and feels larger. The staff were keeping busy, little kids were running around which really made it feel family friendly, warm and inviting. The hostess Chloe was wonderful and extremely polite. Our server Lora H was very nice and checked in on us throughout our meal. The pizza is better made, definitely worth it! Even bought a frozen one to take home!

Sorry about the picture. It doesn‚Äôt do the pizza justice. We just couldn‚Äôt wait to dig in. We picked up a 12 inch Meat Eater and it was fantastic. We are visiting the area for a few days and we were just too tired to cook so we decided to do take out. We searched for pizza near me and this was the first place to pop up, so we decided to try it. Glad we did. Looks like a nice place to dine in as well. We noticed plenty of indoor and outdoor seating as well as a full bar. The staff was super helpful and friendly. We highly recommend Coop‚Äôs Pizza.

This place has great potential as the atmosphere inside and out, is great and it seems like a nice family owned and run restaurant that employs lots of kids (kudos).
We came for the buffet and the pizza was average, making it a hard sell for me to ever order their pizza off the menu instead - we waited 10 minutes for more pizza and the variety wasn‚Äôt good. Crust was too thin to make the pizza enjoyable.
The salad bar had tons of options, and that alone was worth the price. Ultimately $12 for an adult lunch buffet is good bang for your buck in today‚Äôs world.
We were disappointed with the food, but not the service, atmosphere or price!
I love the customer service.  Above and be on for me.... thank you Alana. I'm sorry if I misspelled your name. Love Coops Italian Beef & Pizza, fries, of course the corn nuggets!!
